  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "fgYTC2fLH+qW1hNzLcwwoMD9Duc=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:29.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "## Chat message flow\n\n### 1. Lookup\n\n`lookupUser(bobAddr)` reads `ph:v2:profile:<bob>` to get `{ beeNodePublicKey, overlayAddress }`.\n\n### 2. Live send (PSS)\n\n```\ntopic   = ph:v2:chat:<sorted(alice, bob)>\ntarget  = first 4 chars of bob.overlay\npayload = encrypted({ text, from, chapter, msgId })\n```\n\nA trojan chunk is mined (2-10 s) and lands in Bob's neighborhood. Bob's `pssSubscribe(chatTopic)` decrypts, hands to `ChatManager`, `seenMessageIds` guards duplicates, and the UI updates.\n\n### 3. History persist (debounced, batched pages)\n\n- ACT `uploadFile(page)` to `/bzz` (Bee encrypts via ECDH).\n- Wrapper (64 bytes: `actRef || actHist`) to `/bytes`.\n- Feed update at `ph:v2:chatlog:<sorted(alice, bob)>[:chapter]`.\n- Grantees: `{ alice.beePub, bob.beePub }`.\n\nBob later calls `loadPages(peer=alice)` \u2014 reads feed, fetches wrapper, ACT downloads, merges with his own feed, renders.\n\n### 4. Chapter rotation (clear chat)\n\n`bumpMyChatChapter()` writes `Date.now()` to `swarm:chatMyChapter` in localStorage and clears peer entries in the user manifest. All subsequent PSS messages carry `chapter: <newChapter>`, and peers record and use the new chapter topic for history reads \u2014 a wipe-safe rotation.",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:29.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:29.000Z"
    }
  },
